" r=\"2\"></circle></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Details</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Lucky Number, Day and Color</h2></div></div><div class=\"grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3\"><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Number</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-900\">7</p></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Day</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900\">Saturday</p></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Colors</p><div class=\"mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2\"><span class=\"rounded-full bg-white px-3 py-1 text-sm text-slate-700 ring-1 ring-slate-200\">Gold</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-white px-3 py-1 text-sm text-slate-700 ring-1 ring-slate-200\">Red</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-white px-3 py-1 text-sm text-slate-700 ring-1 ring-slate-200\">Orange</span></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Lucky Stone</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900\">Ruby</p></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Life Path Number</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900\">6</p></div></div><div class=\"mt-4 rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\"><span class=\"font-semibold text-slate-900\">Numerology meaning:</span> <!-- -->Aadavan is a 6 Life Path Number, which represents harmony and balance in all areas of life. This number is associated with love, beauty, and compassion, and those with this number are often natural healers and nurturers.</div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-heart h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M2 9.5a5.5 5.5 0 0 1 9.591-3.676.56.56 0 0 0 .818 0A5.49 5.49 0 0 1 22 9.5c0 2.29-1.5 4-3 5.5l-5.492 5.313a2 2 0 0 1-3 .019L5 15c-1.5-1.5-3-3.2-3-5.5\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Personality</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Personality Traits</h2></div></div><div class=\"flex flex-wrap gap-2\"><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Brave</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Strong</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">V = Virtuous</span></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-book-text h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2H19a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v18a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H6.5a1 1 0 0 1 0-5H20\"></path><path d=\"M8 11h8\"></path><path d=\"M8 7h6\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Spiritual</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Spiritual Significance</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-slate-800 leading-7\">Carrier of divine protection and strength</div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-shield h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Cultural Context</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Cultural Significance</h2></div></div><div class=\"space-y-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\"><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\">The name Aadavan has a rich cultural background as it has been traditionally used in the Hindu community to denote the qualities of strength, courage, and invincibility. It is a name that resonates with the spirit of valor and the proud heritage of being a part of royal or warrior lineage.</div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\">The name Aadavan holds deep spiritual significance as it is closely associated with the powerful Hindu deity Indra. The name carries the blessings of this god of rain, thunder, and power, signifying divine protection, strength, and a strong connection with the divine. The name Aadavan reminds us to be invincible not just in the material world but also in our spiritual journey through life.</div><p class=\"rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-sm text-amber-800\">Cultural Hindu name</p></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-clock h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"></circle><path d=\"M12 6v6l4 2\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Historical Usage</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Historical References</h2></div></div><div class=\"space-y-4\"><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">Aadavan is a divine name associated with Lord Murugan, also known as Subramanya or Kartikeya. He is the god of war, knowledge, and son of Lord Shiva and Goddess Parvati. One of the most significant temples dedicated to Lord Murugan as Aadavan is the Aadhikaraazhadai Alagar Temple located in Madurai, Tamil Nadu, India.</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">6th to 13th Century CE</p></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50 p-4\"><p class=\"text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">The name Aadavan is also mentioned in the ancient Tamil text, Thirumurugatruppadai, which is a collection of hymns devoted to Lord Murugan. This text is believed to have been composed between the 7th and 9th centuries CE.</p><p class=\"mt-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">7th to 9th Century CE</p></div></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-sparkles h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M11.017 2.814a1 1 0 0 1 1.966 0l1.051 5.558a2 2 0 0 0 1.594 1.594l5.558 1.051a1 1 0 0 1 0 1.966l-5.558 1.051a2 2 0 0 0-1.594 1.594l-1.051 5.558a1 1 0 0 1-1.966 0l-1.051-5.558a2 2 0 0 0-1.594-1.594l-5.558-1.051a1 1 0 0 1 0-1.966l5.558-1.051a2 2 0 0 0 1.594-1.594z\"></path><path d=\"M20 2v4\"></path><path d=\"M22 4h-4\"></path><circle cx=\"4\" cy=\"20\" r=\"2\"></circle></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Spiritual</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Spiritual Symbolism</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-slate-800 leading-7\">Aadavan, meaning &#x27;the one who comes first&#x27;, signifies the belief in prioritizing spiritual growth above worldly desires, leading to a purified and enlightened self. This name embodies the Hindu philosophy of dharma, emphasizing the importance of duty, ethics, and righteousness.</div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-trending-up h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M16 7h6v6\"></path><path d=\"m22 7-8.5 8.5-5-5L2 17\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Modern Usage</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Modern Usage</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\">The name &#x27;Aadavan&#x27; is of Hindu origin and is derived from the Tamil language, which means &#x27;the one who comes first&#x27;. It&#x27;s seen on various modern platforms, including social media, where it&#x27;s used as a unique username, profile name, or handles for individuals or communities celebrating Indian culture and Hindu mythology. In the entertainment industry, it&#x27;s used for characters or titles in movies, TV shows, or web series that depict Hindu mythology or Indian culture. For instance, there&#x27;s a 2018 Indian Tamil-language film named &#x27;Aadavan&#x27; that revolves around Hindu mythology. Lastly, in the technology sector, it&#x27;s used for tech startups, apps, or websites that cater to the Indian audience or have a connection to Hindu mythology. For example, there&#x27;s an Indian-origin tech company named &#x27;Aadavan Labs&#x27; that specializes in AI and machine learning.</div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-trending-up h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M16 7h6v6\"></path><path d=\"m22 7-8.5 8.5-5-5L2 17\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Popularity</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Popularity by Region</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\"><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Nepal</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->68</span></div><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Maharashtra</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->67</span></div><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Uttar Pradesh</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->54</span></div><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Mauritius</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->52</span></div></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-award h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m15.477 12.89 1.515 8.526a.5.5 0 0 1-.81.47l-3.58-2.687a1 1 0 0 0-1.197 0l-3.586 2.686a.5.5 0 0 1-.81-.469l1.514-8.526\"></path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"8\" r=\"6\"></circle></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Famous People</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Famous People and Real-World Usage</h2></div></div><p class=\"text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500 mb-3\">Historical Figures &amp; Cultural References</p><div class=\"flex flex-wrap gap-2\"><span class=\"rounded-2xl bg-slate-100 px-3 py-2 text-sm text-slate-700\">Aadavan Malhotra, Indian actor</span><span class=\"rounded-2xl bg-slate-100 px-3 py-2 text-sm text-slate-700\">Aadavan Sivaraman, Tamil film director</span></div></section><section class=\"nv-card-solid\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-languages h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m5 8 6 6\"></path><path d=\"m4 14 6-6 2-3\"></path><path d=\"M2 5h12\"></path><path d=\"M7 2h1\"></path><path d=\"m22 22-5-10-5 10\"></path><path d=\"M14 18h6\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Translations</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Name Translations</h2><p class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-slate-500\">Additional language translations available for this name.</p></div></div><div class=\"grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2\"><div class=\"nv-card-solid p-4\"><div class=\"mb-2 flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900\"><span>🕉️</span><span>Sanskrit</span></div><p class=\"font-semibold text-slate-900\">Aadavan</p><p class=\"mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">हिन्दू नाम जिसका अर्थ है Unconquered, Invincible</p></div><div class=\"nv-card-solid p-4\"><div class=\"mb-2 flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900\"><span>🇮🇳</span><span>Hindi</span></div><p class=\"font-semibold text-slate-900\">आदवान</p><p class=\"mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">अँदरेवार</p></div><div class=\"nv-card-solid p-4\"><div class=\"mb-2 flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900\"><span>🇮🇳</span><span>Tamil</span></div><p class=\"font-semibold text-slate-900\">அடவன்</p><p class=\"mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">அடம் (first) + வான் (leader, chief)</p></div><div class=\"nv-card-solid p-4\"><div class=\"mb-2 flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900\"><span>🇮🇳</span><span>Telugu</span></div><p class=\"font-semibold text-slate-900\">అద్దదన్</p><p class=\"mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-700\">అద్ద (first) + దన్ (leader, chief)</p></div><div class=\"nv-card-solid p-4\"><div class=\"mb-2 flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900\"><span>🇮🇳</span><span>Marathi</span></div><p class=\"font-semibold text-slate-900\">