pe\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/hindu/aadavan#webpage\"},\"about\":{\"@type\":\"DefinedTerm\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/hindu/aadavan#name-term\",\"name\":\"Aadavan\",\"description\":\"Unconquered\"},\"articleSection\":\"Name Meaning\",\"keywords\":\"Aadavan meaning, Aadavan origin, Sanskrit linguistics, Hindu names, pronunciation, lucky number, cultural context\",\"wordCount\":500,\"citation\":{\"@type\":\"CreativeWork\",\"name\":\"NameVerse — Cultural Name Knowledge Base\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\"}}42:[\"$\",\"$L3e\",null,{\"id\":\"scholarly-article-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$47\"}}]\n48:T1fe8,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What does Aadavan mean?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"\\\"Unconquered, Invincible\\\" is the core meaning of Aadavan. Originating from Sanskrit linguistic heritage, this hindu boy name carries semantic depth that connects personal identity to ancestral tradition.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the origin of the name Aadavan?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Aadavan traces its etymological roots to Sanskrit, with documented usage in Hindi and Sanskrit and Marathi and Tamil and Telugu and Bengali. This hindu name reflects centuries of cross-cultural naming exchange.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is Aadavan a boy, girl, or unisex name?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"NameVerse classifies Aadavan as a Male name within hindu naming conventions. Gender associations for names can vary across cultures and historical periods.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How do you pronounce Aadavan?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Speakers pronounce Aadavan as \\\"ah-dah-van\\\" (/aːd̪aːvʌn/). This articulation maintains the Sanskrit sound structure while adapting to English phonetic conventions.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the phonetic transcription of Aadavan?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Using the IPA, Aadavan is written as /aːd̪aːvʌn/. This standardised notation ensures consistent pronunciation across different language backgrounds.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the lucky associations for Aadavan?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"According to Sanskrit naming traditions, Aadavan corresponds to lucky number 7, with Saturday as the most fortunate day, colours Gold and Red and Orange, and Ruby as the lucky gemstone. These associations vary by cultural system.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the numerology of Aadavan?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Numerological analysis of Aadavan yields the number 7 and connects it to Saturday, suggesting Ruby as a complementary stone. Different numerological systems may produce varying interpretations.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What personality traits are associated with Aadavan?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Names like Aadavan in hindu tradition carry connotations of Brave, Strong, V = Virtuous. These personality associations connect the name's meaning to expected character qualities.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the cultural significance of Aadavan?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The cultural significance of Aadavan stems from its Sanskrit roots and hindu context. The name Aadavan has a rich cultural background as it has been traditionally used in the Hindu community to denote the qualities of strength, courage, and invincibility. It is a name that resonates with the spirit of valor and the proud heritage of being a part of royal or warrior lineage. The meaning \\\"Unconquered, Invincible\\\" reinforces the name's place in cultural naming practice.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the spiritual meaning of Aadavan?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The spiritual dimension of Aadavan extends beyond its surface meaning of \\\"Unconquered, Invincible\\\". Within hindu thought, carrier of divine protection and strength\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What names are similar to Aadavan?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Names related to Aadavan include Sagar, Nikhil, Saurav, Vikas, Sunil, Neeraj. These share Sanskrit linguistic roots and often carry comparable meanings or phonetic patterns.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What category does Aadavan belong to?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"In hindu name taxonomy, Aadavan is classified as a Hindu name. Category-based browsing helps identify names with similar stylistic qualities.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Aadavan written in Sanskrit?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Aadavan appears in Sanskrit as \\\"हिन्दू नाम जिसका अर्थ है Unconquered, Invincible\\\". This adaptation preserves the name's essential character while conforming to sanskrit orthographic rules.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Aadavan written in Hindi?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The Hindi equivalent of Aadavan is \\\"अँदरेवार\\\". Such translations show how the name transcends linguistic boundaries while retaining its fundamental meaning.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the historical background of Aadavan?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Documented history of Aadavan states: Aadavan is a divine name associated with Lord Murugan, also known as Subramanya or Kartikeya. He is the god of war, knowledge, and son of Lord Shiva and Goddess Parvati. One of the most significant temples dedicated to Lord Murugan as Aadavan is the Aadhikaraazhadai Alagar Temple located in Madurai, Tamil Nadu, India. This places the name in 6th to 13th Century CE.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-23T06:38:15.193Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}}]}43:[\"$\",\"$L3e\",null,{\"id\":\"faq-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$48\"}}]\n44:[\"$\",\"$L3e\",null,{\"id\":\"breadcrumb-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\"